BENIN – A Criminal Court sitting in Benin City, on Friday, remanded seven suspects over their involvement in the recent cult clash in the Benin metropolis. The seven suspects who were arrested in connection with the resurgence of cult-related clashes in Benin City were remanded in prison custody by Hon. Justice Efe Ikponmwonba, sitting in Criminal Court 1, Benin City. The suspects, namely, Esosa Eregeorowo, Frank Obaze, Minister Godwin, Jeremiah Timothy, Jimoh Lasisi, Osasu Idehen and Idehen Marvis were arraigned for conspiracy to commit murder, murder and membership of an unlawful society. Ruling on an application motion brought by the Prosecutor, the court ordered that the suspects be remanded at the Oko Correctional Centre in Benin City, pending legal advice from the office of the Director of Public prosecution, Edo State. Parading the seven suspects earlier, Edo state police command spokesman, Chidi Nwanbuzor saidEsosa Eregborowo and Frank Obazee were arrested at Iguosodin Community Upper Siluko Road Benin city. Nwanbuzor said Minister Godwin and Jeremiah Timothy were botharrested at Eweka by Siluko Road, Benin City while Lasisi Jimoh, Idehen Osazu and Idehen Mavis who confessed to being members of the Eiye secret cult were also arrested at Siluko road, Benin city.